      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Dr Pippa Malmgren was appointed as a Non-Executive Board Member of the Department for International Trade in November 2016.</p>

<p>Dr Malmgren is the founder of DRPM Group, which helps clients better anticipate trends in the world economy.</p>

<p>Pippa is also:</p>

<ul>
  <li>the co-founder of H Robotics, a company which produces aerial platform drones for commercial firms</li>
  <li>author of a geopolitical book ‘Signals: How Everyday Signs Can Help Us Navigate the World’s Turbulent Economy (2016)’</li>
</ul>

<p>Previously, Dr Malmgren was Special Assistant to the President of the United States, during which she served on the National Economic Council and was a member of President’s Working Group on Financial Markets and the Working Group on Corporate Governance.</p>

<p>Her previous roles include:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Chief Currency Strategist at Bankers Trust</li>
  <li>Deputy Head of Global Strategy at UBS</li>
</ul>
</div>
      </section>

